text: Christian Ménard (born April 7, 1946 in Quimper, Finistère) is a member of the National Assembly of France. He represents the Finistère department, and is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1946 births Category:Living people Category:People from Quimper Category:Politicians from Brittany Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:University of Nantes alumni Category:French physicians
